AddApplicationAccountToUser.summary: 在当前应用下给指定员工添加一个应用账号。

AddUserToOrganizationalUnits.title: AddUserToOrganizationalUnits
AddUserToOrganizationalUnits.summary: Adds an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) account to multiple EIAM organizations of Identity as a Service (IDaaS). If the account already exists in the organizational unit, the system directly returns a success response.

AddUsersToGroup.title: AddUsersToGroup
AddUsersToGroup.summary: Adds Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) accounts to an EIAM group of Identity as a Service (IDaaS).

AuthorizeApplicationToGroups.title: AuthorizeApplicationToGroups
AuthorizeApplicationToGroups.summary: Grants the permissions to access an application to multiple account groups at a time in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM).

AuthorizeApplicationToOrganizationalUnit.title: AuthorizeApplicationToOrganizationalUnits
AuthorizeApplicationToOrganizationalUnit.summary: Grants the access permissions on an application to multiple Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) organizations at a time.

AuthorizeApplicationToUsers.title: AuthorizeApplicationToUsers
AuthorizeApplicationToUsers.summary: Grants the access permissions on an application to multiple Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) accounts at a time.

CreateApplication.title: CreateApplication
CreateApplication.summary: Adds an application to an Enterprise Identity Access Management (EIAM) instance of Identity as a Service (IDaaS).

CreateApplicationClientSecret.title: CreateApplicationClientSecret
CreateApplicationClientSecret.summary: Creates a client key for an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) application. An EIAM application can have up to two client keys.

CreateDomain.title: CreateDomain
CreateDomain.summary: Creates a custom domain name for an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance.

CreateDomainProxyToken.title: CreateDomainProxyToken
CreateDomainProxyToken.summary: Creates a proxy token for a domain name of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance.

CreateGroup.title: CreateGroup
CreateGroup.summary: Creates an account group in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM).

CreateInstance.title: CreateInstance
CreateInstance.summary: Creates an instance based on which all capabilities of Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Enterprise Identity and Access Management (EIAM) are provided.

CreateOrganizationalUnit.title: CreateOrganizationalUnit
CreateOrganizationalUnit.summary: Creates an organization in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM).

CreateUser.title: CreateUser
CreateUser.summary: Creates an account in an Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Enterprise Identity Access Management (EIAM) instance.

DeleteApplication.title: DeleteApplication
DeleteApplication.summary: Deletes an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) application.

DeleteApplicationClientSecret.title: DeleteApplicationClientSecret
DeleteApplicationClientSecret.summary: Deletes a client key for an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) application.

DeleteDomain.title: DeleteDomain
DeleteDomain.summary: Deletes a custom domain name of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance. You cannot delete the initial domain name and default domain name of the instance.

DeleteDomainProxyToken.title: DeleteDomainProxyToken
DeleteDomainProxyToken.summary: Deletes a proxy token for a domain name of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance. Only the proxy tokens in the disabled state can be deleted.

DeleteGroup.title: DeleteGroup
DeleteGroup.summary: Deletes the information of an account group in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM).

DeleteInstance.title: DeleteInstance
DeleteInstance.summary: Deletes an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance of Identity as a Service (IDaaS) that you do not need.

DeleteNetworkAccessEndpoint.title: DeleteNetworkAccessEndpoint
DeleteNetworkAccessEndpoint.summary: Delete a network endpoint of a specific type.

DeleteOrganizationalUnit.title: DeleteOrganizationalUnit
DeleteOrganizationalUnit.summary: Deletes an organization in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM). If the organization has EIAM accounts or child organizations, the delete operation fails.

DeleteOrganizationalUnitChildren.title: DeleteOrganizationalUnitChildren
DeleteOrganizationalUnitChildren.summary: Deletes information about an organization and forcefully deletes all accounts and sub-organizations in the organization.

DeleteUser.title: DeleteUser
DeleteUser.summary: Deletes an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) account of Identity as a Service (IDaaS). The information related to the account is cleared.

DisableApplication.title: DisableApplication
DisableApplication.summary: Disables an enabled Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) application. All features of the EIAM application cannot be used if you disable the EIAM application.

DisableApplicationApiInvoke.title: DisableApplicationApiInvoke
DisableApplicationApiInvoke.summary: Disables the Developer API feature for an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) application.

DisableApplicationClientSecret.title: DisableApplicationClientSecret
DisableApplicationClientSecret.summary: Disables a client key of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) application.

DisableApplicationProvisioning.title: DisableApplicationProvisioning
DisableApplicationProvisioning.summary: Disables the account synchronization feature for an application in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM).

DisableApplicationSso.title: DisableApplicationSso
DisableApplicationSso.summary: Disables the single sign-on (SSO) feature for an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) application. This way, employees cannot log on to the application by using SSO.

DisableDomainProxyToken.title: DisableDomainProxyToken
DisableDomainProxyToken.summary: Disables a proxy token for a domain name of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance. After the proxy token is disabled, the domain name may not be used as expected.

DisableInitDomainAutoRedirect.title: DisableInitDomainAutoRedirect
DisableInitDomainAutoRedirect.summary: Disables the feature of automatically redirecting the initial domain name to the default domain name for an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance. After the feature is disabled, users who visit the portal page by using the initial domain name are not redirected to the default domain name.

DisableUser.title: DisableUser
DisableUser.summary: Disables an Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) account. If the account is disabled, a success message is returned.

EnableApplication.title: EnableApplication
EnableApplication.summary: Enables a disabled Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) application.

EnableApplicationApiInvoke.title: EnableApplicationApiInvoke
EnableApplicationApiInvoke.summary: Enables the Developer API feature for an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) application.

EnableApplicationClientSecret.title: EnableApplicationClientSecret
EnableApplicationClientSecret.summary: Enables the client key of an application in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM).

EnableApplicationProvisioning.title: EnableApplicationProvisioning
EnableApplicationProvisioning.summary: Enables the account synchronization feature for an application in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM).

EnableApplicationSso.title: EnableApplicationSso
EnableApplicationSso.summary: Enables the single sign-on (SSO) feature for an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) application.

EnableDomainProxyToken.title: EnableDomainProxyToken
EnableDomainProxyToken.summary: Enables a proxy token for a domain name of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance. The proxy token is used to verify the security of the domain name.

EnableInitDomainAutoRedirect.title: EnableInitDomainAutoRedirect
EnableInitDomainAutoRedirect.summary: Enables the feature of automatically redirecting the initial domain name to the default domain name for an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance.

EnableUser.title: EnableUser
EnableUser.summary: Enables an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) account of Identity as a Service (IDaaS).

GetApplication.title: GetApplication
GetApplication.summary: Queries the details of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) application.

GetApplicationGrantScope.title: GetApplicationGrantScope
GetApplicationGrantScope.summary: Queries the permissions of the Developer API feature for an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) application.

GetApplicationProvisioningConfig.title: GetApplicationProvisioningConfig
GetApplicationProvisioningConfig.summary: Queries the configuration of the account synchronization feature for an application in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM).

GetApplicationProvisioningScope.title: GetApplicationProvisioningScope
GetApplicationProvisioningScope.summary: Queries the account synchronization scope of applications in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee IAM (EIAM). This scope is the same as the scope within which developers can call the DeveloperAPI to query and manage accounts.

GetApplicationSsoConfig.title: GetApplicationSsoConfig
GetApplicationSsoConfig.summary: Queries the single sign-on (SSO) configuration attributes of an application in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee IAM (EIAM).

GetDomain.title: GetDomain
GetDomain.summary: Queries the information about a domain name of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance.

GetDomainDnsChallenge.title: GetDomainDnsChallenge
GetDomainDnsChallenge.summary: Queries the domain name system (DNS) challenge records of a domain name of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance. The generated records are used to verify the ownership of the domain name.

GetForgetPasswordConfiguration.title: GetForgetPasswordConfiguration
GetForgetPasswordConfiguration.summary: Queries the forgot password configurations of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance of Identity as a Service (IDaaS).

GetGroup.title: GetGroup
GetGroup.summary: Queries the information of an account group in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM).

GetIdentityProviderUdPullConfiguration.title: GetIdentityProviderUdPullConfiguration
GetIdentityProviderUdPullConfiguration.summary: Get IdP Inbound Synchronization Configuration Information

GetInstance.title: GetInstance
GetInstance.summary: Queries the information of an Enterprise Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance of Identity as a Service (IDaaS).

GetInstanceLicense.title: Query License of the Instance
GetInstanceLicense.summary: Query the currently effective License information of the instance

GetOrganizationalUnit.title: GetOrganizationalUnit
GetOrganizationalUnit.summary: Queries the information about an organizational unit in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee IAM (EIAM).

GetPasswordComplexityConfiguration.title: GetPasswordComplexityConfiguration
GetPasswordComplexityConfiguration.summary: Queries the password complexity configurations of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance of Identity as a Service (IDaaS).

GetPasswordExpirationConfiguration.title: GetPasswordExpirationConfiguration
GetPasswordExpirationConfiguration.summary: Queries the password expiration configurations of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance of Identity as a Service (IDaaS).

GetPasswordHistoryConfiguration.title: GetPasswordHistoryConfiguration
GetPasswordHistoryConfiguration.summary: Queries the password history configurations of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance of Identity as a Service (IDaaS).

GetPasswordInitializationConfiguration.title: GetPasswordInitializationConfiguration
GetPasswordInitializationConfiguration.summary: Queries the password initialization configurations of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance of Identity as a Service (IDaaS).

GetRootOrganizationalUnit.title: GetRootOrganizationalUnit
GetRootOrganizationalUnit.summary: Queries the information about the root organizational unit in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM).

GetSynchronizationJob.title: GetSynchronizationJob
GetSynchronizationJob.summary: Obtains the information about a single synchronization job.

GetUser.title: GetUser
GetUser.summary: Queries the details of an account in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee IAM (EIAM).

ListApplicationClientSecrets.title: ListApplicationClientSecrets
ListApplicationClientSecrets.summary: Queries all client keys of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) application. The returned key secret is not masked. If you want to query the key secret that is masked, call the ObtainApplicationClientSecret operation.

ListApplicationSupportedProvisionProtoco.title: ListApplicationSupportedProvisionProtocolTypes
ListApplicationSupportedProvisionProtoco.summary: Queries the synchronization protocol types that are supported by an application.

ListApplications.title: ListApplications
ListApplications.summary: Queries the information about one or multiple Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) applications by page.

ListApplicationsForOrganizationalUnit.title: ListApplicationsForOrganizationalUnit
ListApplicationsForOrganizationalUnit.summary: Queries the applications that an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) organization can access. The return result includes the IDs of the applications. If you want to obtain the details of the applications, call the GetApplication operation.

ListApplicationsForUser.title: ListApplicationsForUser
ListApplicationsForUser.summary: Queries the applications that an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) account can access. The return result includes the IDs of the applications. If you want to obtain the details of the applications, call the GetApplication operation.

ListConditionalAccessPoliciesForNetworkZ.title: List Conditional Access Policies Associated with Network Zones
ListConditionalAccessPoliciesForNetworkZ.summary: List Conditional Access Policies Associated with Network Areas

ListDomainProxyTokens.title: ListDomainProxyTokens
ListDomainProxyTokens.summary: Queries the proxy tokens of a domain name of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance.

ListDomains.title: ListDomains
ListDomains.summary: Queries a list of domain names of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance. The list contains the initial domain name and custom domain names.

ListEiamInstances.title: ListEiamInstances
ListEiamInstances.summary: Queries the information about Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) V1.0 instances or EIAM V2.0 instances.

ListEiamRegions.title: ListEiamRegions
ListEiamRegions.summary: Queries the regions in which Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) V1.0 instances or EIAM V2.0 instances reside.

ListGroups.title: ListGroups
ListGroups.summary: Queries a list of account groups in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM).

ListGroupsForApplication.title: ListGroupsForApplication
ListGroupsForApplication.summary: Queries the account groups that are granted permissions to access an application and displays the results by page. The IDs of the account groups are returned. To query the detailed information about the account groups, call the GetGroup operation.

ListGroupsForUser.title: ListGroupsForUser
ListGroupsForUser.summary: Queries a list of account groups to which an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) account of Identity as a Service (IDaaS) belongs.

ListIdentityProviders.title: ListIdentityProviders
ListIdentityProviders.summary: Query the list of identity providers.

ListInstances.title: ListInstances
ListInstances.summary: Queries the information about one or more Enterprise Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instances of Identity as a Service (IDaaS).

ListNetworkAccessEndpointAvailableRegion.title: ListNetworkAccessEndpointAvailableRegions
ListNetworkAccessEndpointAvailableRegion.summary: Get a list of regions that support network access endpoints.

ListNetworkAccessEndpointAvailableZones.title: ListNetworkAccessEndpointAvailableZones
ListNetworkAccessEndpointAvailableZones.summary: Queries the zones that support dedicated network endpoints in the specified region of Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM).

ListNetworkAccessPaths.title: ListNetworkAccessPaths
ListNetworkAccessPaths.summary: List the access paths under a certain network access endpoint.

ListOrganizationalUnitParents.title: ListOrganizationalUnitParents
ListOrganizationalUnitParents.summary: Queries all parent organizations of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) organization.

ListOrganizationalUnits.title: ListOrganizationalUnits
ListOrganizationalUnits.summary: Queries the information about organizational units in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee IAM (EIAM) by page.

ListOrganizationalUnitsForApplication.title: ListOrganizationalUnitsForApplication
ListOrganizationalUnitsForApplication.summary: Queries the organizations that are allowed to access an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) application by page. The return result includes the IDs of the organizations. If you want to obtain the details of the organizations, call the GetOrganizationalUnit operation.

ListRegions.title: ListRegions
ListRegions.summary: Queries a list of supported Alibaba Cloud regions.

ListSynchronizationJobs.title: ListSynchronizationJobs
ListSynchronizationJobs.summary: Queries a list of synchronization jobs.

ListUsers.title: ListUsers
ListUsers.summary: Queries the details of accounts in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee IAM (EIAM) by page.

ListUsersForApplication.title: ListUsersForApplication
ListUsersForApplication.summary: Queries the accounts that are allowed to access an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) application. The return results include the IDs of the accounts. If you need to obtain the details of the accounts, call the GetUser operation.

ListUsersForGroup.title: ListUsersForGroup
ListUsersForGroup.summary: Queries the information of accounts in an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) group of Identity as a Service (IDaaS).

ObtainApplicationClientSecret.title: ObtainApplicationClientSecret
ObtainApplicationClientSecret.summary: Queries a client key of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) application. The returned key secret is masked. If you want to query the key secret that is not masked, call the ListApplicationClientSecrets operation.

ObtainDomainProxyToken.title: ObtainDomainProxyToken
ObtainDomainProxyToken.summary: Queries the information about a proxy token of a domain name of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance.

RemoveUserFromOrganizationalUnits.title: RemoveUserFromOrganizationalUnits
RemoveUserFromOrganizationalUnits.summary: Removes an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) account from multiple EIAM organizations of Identity as a Service (IDaaS). You cannot remove an account from a primary organization.

RemoveUsersFromGroup.title: RemoveUsersFromGroup
RemoveUsersFromGroup.summary: Removes Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) accounts from an EIAM group of Identity as a Service (IDaaS).

RevokeApplicationFromGroups.title: RevokeApplicationFromGroups
RevokeApplicationFromGroups.summary: Revokes the permissions to access an application from multiple account groups at a time in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM).

RevokeApplicationFromOrganizationalUnits.title: RevokeApplicationFromOrganizationalUnits
RevokeApplicationFromOrganizationalUnits.summary: Revokes the permissions to access an application from multiple Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) organizations at a time.

RevokeApplicationFromUsers.title: RevokeApplicationFromUsers
RevokeApplicationFromUsers.summary: Revokes the permissions to access an application from multiple Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) accounts at a time.

RunSynchronizationJob.title: RunSynchronizationJob
RunSynchronizationJob.summary: Creates a synchronization job and immediately runs the job.

SetApplicationGrantScope.title: SetApplicationGrantScope
SetApplicationGrantScope.summary: Configures the permissions of the Developer API feature of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) application.

SetApplicationProvisioningConfig.title: SetApplicationProvisioningConfig
SetApplicationProvisioningConfig.summary: Configures the account synchronization feature for an application in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM).

SetApplicationProvisioningScope.title: SetApplicationProvisioningScope
SetApplicationProvisioningScope.summary: Sets the account synchronization scope of applications in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee IAM (EIAM). This scope is the same as the scope within which developers can call the DeveloperAPI to query and manage accounts.

SetApplicationSsoConfig.title: SetApplicationSsoConfig
SetApplicationSsoConfig.summary: Specifies the single sign-on (SSO) configuration attributes of an application in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee IAM (EIAM).

SetDefaultDomain.title: SetDefaultDomain
SetDefaultDomain.summary: Sets a domain name of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance as the default domain name.

SetForgetPasswordConfiguration.title: SetForgetPasswordConfiguration
SetForgetPasswordConfiguration.summary: Configures a forgot password policy for an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance of Identity as a Service (IDaaS).

SetPasswordComplexityConfiguration.title: SetPasswordComplexityConfiguration
SetPasswordComplexityConfiguration.summary: Configures a password complexity policy for an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance of Identity as a Service (IDaaS).

SetPasswordExpirationConfiguration.title: SetPasswordExpirationConfiguration
SetPasswordExpirationConfiguration.summary: Configures a password expiration policy for an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance of Identity as a Service (IDaaS).

SetPasswordHistoryConfiguration.title: SetPasswordHistoryConfiguration
SetPasswordHistoryConfiguration.summary: Configures a password history policy for an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance of Identity as a Service (IDaaS).

SetPasswordInitializationConfiguration.title: SetPasswordInitializationConfiguration
SetPasswordInitializationConfiguration.summary: Sets the password initialization configurations for an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance of Identity as a Service (IDaaS).

SetUserPrimaryOrganizationalUnit.title: SetUserPrimaryOrganizationalUnit
SetUserPrimaryOrganizationalUnit.summary: Updates the primary organizational unit to which an Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) account belongs. This account will be removed from the previous primary organizational unit and added to the new primary organization.

UnlockUser.title: UnlockUser
UnlockUser.summary: Unlocks an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) account of Identity as a Service (IDaaS) that is locked.

UpdateApplicationAuthorizationType.title: UpdateApplicationAuthorizationType
UpdateApplicationAuthorizationType.summary: Modifies the authorization type of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) application.

UpdateApplicationDescription.title: UpdateApplicationDescription
UpdateApplicationDescription.summary: Modifies the description of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) application.

UpdateGroup.title: UpdateGroup
UpdateGroup.summary: Updates the information about an account group in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM). If the information is empty, the information is not updated by default.

UpdateGroupDescription.title: UpdateGroupDescription
UpdateGroupDescription.summary: Updates the description of an Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) account group.

UpdateInstanceDescription.title: UpdateInstanceDescription
UpdateInstanceDescription.summary: Modifies the description of an Enterprise Identity and Access Management (EIAM) instance of Identity as a Service (IDaaS).

UpdateOrganizationalUnit.title: UpdateOrganizationalUnit
UpdateOrganizationalUnit.summary: Updates the basic information about an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) organization. The basic information about the organization is not updated by default if no parameter is specified.

UpdateOrganizationalUnitDescription.title: UpdateOrganizationalUnitDescription
UpdateOrganizationalUnitDescription.summary: Modifies the description of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) organization.

UpdateOrganizationalUnitParentId.title: UpdateOrganizationalUnitParentId
UpdateOrganizationalUnitParentId.summary: Updates the parent organization ID of an organization in Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM). In this case, the organization is moved from a parent node to a new node.

UpdateUser.title: UpdateUser
UpdateUser.summary: Updates the basic information about an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) account of Identity as a Service (IDaaS).

UpdateUserDescription.title: UpdateUserDescription
UpdateUserDescription.summary: Modifies the description of an Identity as a Service (IDaaS) Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) account.

UpdateUserPassword.title: UpdateUserPassword
UpdateUserPassword.summary: Updates the password information of an Employee Identity and Access Management (EIAM) account of Identity as a Service (IDaaS). The password must meet the requirements of the password policies that are configured in the IDaaS console.
